Catlin Painter
Mons. s Street
13. Rue Tronchit?
with Ayer N A Ms 146

Dear Sir,
The Bearer will bring my Album, unless on further thought you would like to keep it for Lb. 30 instead of Lb 35 which I named.
My absolute want of a little to move on with, impelled me to offer to you what I never before thought of parting with.
Yours sincerely,
Geo. Catlin
Ayers N. A. Ms. 146

Utica --- --- 1827
Dear Sir,
I wrote & sent you a letter a few days since from this place, and since its dep-- 2 turn home we  O yours of the 24th ----, which was forwarded from Albany.
The "Commision" named in it is flattering to me, and, though I refuse all orders, I wil attend to this in the best manner that I can, though it may be somewhat inconvenient for me to do so. I have had withing the last year more orders than I could have painted but I have refused all of them, as I have more of my own orders than I can attend to for some time to come.
I have but a moment to spare, as the Bearer of this waits -
Our best wishes for thee & thine.
truly yours
Geo. Catlin
Ayer N A Ma 146
